          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Λυκόοργος</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Λυκοϝ</span>.): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">Lycurgus.</span>— (1) son of
          Dryas, king of the Edonians in Thrace, banishes from his land the
          worship of Dionȳsus (Bacchus), <i><span class="en">Il.
            6.134</span></i>. —(2) an Arcadian, slays Arithous, <i><span class="en">Il. 7.142</span></i>-148.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
